data.title: Asya Fateyeva & Saarland State Orchestra: To the Muse (Official Album Trailer)
data.meta_description: „A sensation for the music world.“ – Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung „The young Asya Fateyeva plays alto saxophone so elegantly and masterfully that the beauty of the sound she conjures in Debussy's Rhapsody for Saxophone and Piano enchants everyone.“ – Harald Eggebrecht, Süddeutsche Zeitung
data.text:
„A sensation for the music world.“

– Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung

„The young Asya Fateyeva plays alto saxophone so elegantly and masterfully that the beauty of the sound she conjures in Debussy's Rhapsody for Saxophone and Piano enchants everyone.“

– Harald Eggebrecht, Süddeutsche Zeitung

Accompanied by Luise Enzian on the baroque harp, Asya Fateyeva plays arrangements for her instrument, melodies from the German and Italian Baroque as well as contemporary music, such as "Hope Is a Dangerous Thing for a Woman Like Me to Have" by the American singer-songwriter Lana Del Rey. Fateyeva does justice to Adolphe Sax's invention. She is one of the best in her field.

Asya Fateyeva sees no limits for her instrument and constantly brings the saxophone back into the focus of the music world: with innovative programs and great skill. In this arte documentary, viewers experience how she thrills classical audiences at the Elbphilharmonie and go on a documentary journey with her.
